Fixed code: We change `break` to `continue`. Also, we should ensure that the `else if` block does not add the option. That's already achieved by `continue`. But what about the case where we do not `continue`? Actually, if the value is positive, we skip the `else if` block and go to `cmd.addOption(opt)`. That's correct. If the value is negative, we enter the `else if` block and execute `continue`, which jumps to the next iteration, skipping `cmd.addOption(opt)`. Good.

One more thing: The `else if` block currently only has `break;`. After changing to `continue;`, we need to make sure there is no other code after the `else if` that should be skipped. There isn't.

Thus the fixed function:

```
    protected void processProperties(Properties properties)
    {
        if (properties == null)
        {
            return;
        }

        for (Enumeration e = properties.propertyNames(); e.hasMoreElements();)
        {
            String option = e.nextElement().toString();

            if (!cmd.hasOption(option))
            {
                Option opt = getOptions().getOption(option);

                // get the value from the properties instance
                String value = properties.getProperty(option);

                if (opt.hasArg())
                {
                    if (opt.getValues() == null || opt.getValues().length == 0)
                    {
                        try
                        {
                            opt.addValueForProcessing(value);
                        }
                        catch (RuntimeException exp)
                        {
                            // if we cannot add the value don't worry about it
                        }
                    }
                }
                else if (!("yes".equalsIgnoreCase(value)
                        || "true".equalsIgnoreCase(value)
                        || "1".equalsIgnoreCase(value)))
                {
                    // if the value is not yes, true or 1 then don't add the
                    // option to the CommandLine
                    continue;
                }

                cmd.addOption(opt);
            }
        }
    }
```

